      1. Create a new 100MB physical partition mounted under /testfolder. Create the folder, if it doesn’t exist.
      2. Create a new 250MB swap partition.
      3. Create a new physical volume, create a new volume group named ‘datacenter’, where the
      extent size is 16MB. Create a logical volume named ’test_lv’ with the size of 50 extents and file system ext4,
      then mount it under /datasource.
      4. Create a volume group called "test_vg", the volume group consists of 2 physical volumes, 300MB each.
      Create a logical volume called "lv_1" with the size of 400MB, filesystem "ext3", and permanently mounted under /mylvm.
